# Concurrent Log Analytics Engine

A high-performance log processing and analytics system built using **C++17**. The engine processes large log datasets concurrently using asynchronous task execution, extracts insights through regex-based parsing, and generates statistical reports through a modular and scalable architecture.

## 🚀 Features

- Concurrent log processing using `std::async` and `std::future`
- Parallel workload distribution for improved performance
- Regex-based log parsing and analysis
- Statistical aggregation of log data
- Modular object-oriented architecture
- Robust file handling and exception management
- Automated report generation
- Modern C++17 implementation

---

## 🏗️ Architecture

```text
                +------------------+
                |     main.cpp     |
                +--------+---------+
                         |
                         v
                +------------------+
                |   LogAnalyzer    |
                +--------+---------+
                         |
         +---------------+---------------+
         |                               |
         v                               v
+------------------+          +------------------+
|   ThreadWorker   |          |    Statistics    |
| Log Processing   |          | Data Aggregation |
+------------------+          +------------------+
         |
         v
+------------------+
| ReportGenerator  |
+------------------+
```

### Components

#### LogAnalyzer
- Reads log files
- Splits data into chunks
- Launches asynchronous tasks
- Aggregates worker results

#### ThreadWorker
- Processes log chunks
- Performs regex-based parsing
- Extracts and categorizes log entries

#### Statistics
- Stores analytics metrics
- Merges results from workers
- Maintains aggregated statistics

#### ReportGenerator
- Generates summarized reports
- Displays analysis results

